<TITLE> Nation mourns officers killed in chopper crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 10 (bdnews24.com)  The nation Wednesday was mourning the two senior army officers, including Jessore's GOC, who died in Monday's helicopter crash at Tangail. Maj Gen Rafiqul Islam, general officer commanding of Jessore-based 55 Infantry Division, and pilot Lt Col Shahidul Islam were killed when their helicopter crashed at Rouhat in Kalihati Upazila at around 8am Monday after hitting power lines. Injured co-pilot Major Saif is being treated at the Combined Military Hospital in Dhaka Cantonment. Namaj-e-janaza will be held Wednesday for Maj Gen Rafiqul and Lt Col Shahid, as well as two officers, Col Gulzar Uddin Ahmed and Lt Col Manzur-e-Elahi Chowdhury, who were killed in the BDR mutiny last month. The bodies of Col Gulzar Uddin Ahmed and Lt Col Manzur-e-Elahi were identified Tuesday, almost two weeks after their deaths, through DNA tests and fingerprint matching, repsectively. The janaza will be held at the Army Stadium at 4pm. bdne
